  "prompt": "Does the law differentiate between intentional and unintentional money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, the law typically distinguishes between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering involves deliberate actions to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds, while unintentional money laundering may occur through negligence or lack of proper due diligence. The intent and knowledge of the person involved can significantly impact the legal consequences and potential penalties.\n\nIntentional money laundering is generally prosecuted more severely, with potential criminal charges and more significant legal consequences. Unintentional money laundering might result in civil penalties or administrative actions, depending on the specific circumstances and jurisdictional laws.",
